20 (b) Promote positive behavior by pupils, prevent disciplinary practices that
21 are exclusionary and support equitable outcomes for all pupils by utilizing:
22 (1) A framework of social, emotional and positive behavioral supports
23 that progresses from universal screenings, programs and activities for all pupils
24 to targeted supports for subgroups of pupils to individualized plans for specific
25 pupils who need the most social, emotional or positive behavioral supports; and
26 (2) Evidence-based practices.
